abstract: With the timing of a final impeachment vote still up in the air, President Donald Trump plans to deliver his State of the Union address to a joint session of Congress on Tuesday and focus on a U.S. economic boom that he hopes will spur his re-election.
snippet: With the timing of a final impeachment vote still up in the air, President Donald Trump plans to deliver his State of the Union address to a joint session of Congress on Tuesday and focus on a U.S. economic boom that he hopes will spur his re-elec...
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — With the timing of a final impeachment vote still up in the air, President Donald Trump plans to deliver his State of the Union address to a joint session of Congress on Tuesday and focus on a U.S. economic boom that he hopes will spur his re-election.
headline_main: Echoing His Campaign Pitch, Trump Will Focus on Economic Boom in Annual Speech
headline_print_headline: Echoing His Campaign Pitch, Trump Will Focus on Economic Boom in Annual Speech

abstract: Iraq's leading Shi'ite cleric, Grand Ayatollah Ali al-Sistani, on Friday condemned the use of force to disperse protest camps across the country, as security forces stepped up a crackdown against demonstrators.
snippet: Iraq's leading Shi'ite cleric, Grand Ayatollah Ali al-Sistani, on Friday condemned the use of force to disperse protest camps across the country, as security forces stepped up a crackdown against demonstrators.
lead_paragraph: BAGHDAD — Iraq's leading Shi'ite cleric, Grand Ayatollah Ali al-Sistani, on Friday condemned the use of force to disperse protest camps across the country, as security forces stepped up a crackdown against demonstrators.
headline_main: Iraq Top Cleric Condemns Use of Force Against Protest Camps, Urges Early Election
headline_print_headline: Iraq Top Cleric Condemns Use of Force Against Protest Camps, Urges Early Election

abstract: Turkish President Tayyip Erdogan on Friday criticised Saudi Arabia and other Gulf Arab nations for not speaking out against the U.S. Middle East plan which he said endorsed the Israeli annexation of Palestinian lands.
snippet: Turkish President Tayyip Erdogan on Friday criticised Saudi Arabia and other Gulf Arab nations for not speaking out against the U.S. Middle East plan which he said endorsed the Israeli annexation of Palestinian lands.
lead_paragraph: ANKARA — Turkish President Tayyip Erdogan on Friday criticised Saudi Arabia and other Gulf Arab nations for not speaking out against the U.S. Middle East plan which he said endorsed the Israeli annexation of Palestinian lands.
headline_main: Turkey's Erdogan Criticises Arab Silence Over U.S. Middle East Plan
headline_print_headline: Turkey's Erdogan Criticises Arab Silence Over U.S. Middle East Plan

abstract: More Republicans announced opposition on Friday to calling witnesses in President Donald Trump's U.S. Senate impeachment trial, dooming a bid by Democrats to permit testimony and paving the way for his expected acquittal.
snippet: More Republicans announced opposition on Friday to calling witnesses in President Donald Trump's U.S. Senate impeachment trial, dooming a bid by Democrats to permit testimony and paving the way for his expected acquittal.
lead_paragraph: (Reuters) - More Republicans announced opposition on Friday to calling witnesses in President Donald Trump's U.S. Senate impeachment trial, dooming a bid by Democrats to permit testimony and paving the way for his expected acquittal.
headline_main: 'No Fair Trial': Quotes From Trump's Senate Impeachment Trial
headline_print_headline: 'No Fair Trial': Quotes From Trump's Senate Impeachment Trial

abstract: Former New York City Mayor Michael Bloomberg contributed more than $200 million (£152.16 million) of his own money to his bid for the Democratic presidential nomination as of the end of 2019, according to disclosures his campaign filed on Friday with the Federal Election Commission.
snippet: Former New York City Mayor Michael Bloomberg contributed more than $200 million (£152.16 million) of his own money to his bid for the Democratic presidential nomination as of the end of 2019, according to disclosures his campaign filed on Friday w...
lead_paragraph: (Reuters) - Former New York City Mayor Michael Bloomberg contributed more than $200 million (£152.16 million) of his own money to his bid for the Democratic presidential nomination as of the end of 2019, according to disclosures his campaign filed on Friday with the Federal Election Commission.
headline_main: U.S. Candidate Bloomberg Spent $200 Million of Own Wealth on Presidential Bid in 2019

abstract: The diabolical duo of Donald and Mitch, serving their own interests, not the national one.
snippet: The diabolical duo of Donald and Mitch, serving their own interests, not the national one.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — During a meeting with Donald Trump at Trump Tower in June of 2016, with the opéra bouffe builder improbably heading toward the nomination despite a skeletal campaign crew on a floor below, I asked when he would pivot.
